---
import BaseLayout from "~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  lang="en"
  title="Join Us"
  description="Information for prospective students and collaborators interested in joining the Thermoacoustic Lab."
>
  <section class="py-8">
    <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-brand-500">Join Us</p>
    <h1 class="mt-2 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-brand-900">
      Join Us
    </h1>
    <div class="mt-3 h-1 w-16 bg-accent-500" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  </section>

  <section class="mt-8 max-w-3xl space-y-5 text-gray-700">
    <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed">
      If you are considering joining the Thermoacoustic Lab — whether you are
      preparing for graduate-school admission, looking to do an undergraduate
      research project, or already accepted and weighing your options — this
      page is for you.
    </p>
    <div class="mt-8 rounded-lg border-l-4 border-accent-500 bg-brand-50 p-6">
      <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-widest text-brand-500">
        Quick start
      </p>
      <p class="mt-2 text-brand-900">
        Email the PI with your inquiry:
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        <a
          href="mailto:bookhsu@ntut.edu.tw"
          class="text-lg text-accent-600 underline hover:text-accent-700"
          >bookhsu@ntut.edu.tw</a
        >
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-gray-600">
        Subject line:
        <code class="rounded bg-white px-2 py-0.5 font-mono text-sm text-brand-800">
          [Lab Application] Your Name / University / Year
        </code>
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">
        For prospective MS students
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Before our meeting, please prepare an <strong>A4 one-pager</strong> as a
        starting point for our conversation — this saves time on background and
        lets us dive into the research itself. Useful items:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Undergraduate transcript</strong>: major coursework and
            class rank (if available).
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Undergraduate research project</strong>: topic, what you
            did, results, and what you took away.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Skills</strong>: programming languages, experimental
            techniques, measurement / analysis tools or software.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Initial research direction</strong>: your early thoughts on
            thermoacoustics, fluid mechanics, or energy systems — tell me what
            you'd like to work on.
          </span>
        </li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-brand-900">
        For prospective undergraduate researchers
      </h2>
      <p class="mt-3">
        Undergraduate researchers in the lab are expected to keep building the
        following foundations during their time with us:
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 pl-5">
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Mechanical fabrication</strong>: basic machine-shop
            operations and workflow.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Programming fundamentals</strong>: scripting languages
            (e.g., Python, Julia) for data processing and measurement
            automation.
          </span>
        </li>
        <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
          <span class="mt-2 inline-block h-1.5 w-1.5 shrink-0 rounded-full bg-accent-500"></span>
          <span>
            <strong>Undergraduate-level math &amp; physics</strong>: mechanics,
            fluid mechanics, thermodynamics, vibration analysis.
          </span>
        </li>
      </ul>
      <p class="mt-4">
        <strong>Goals.</strong> Each year, we aim to publish at the
        <strong>annual conference of the Chinese Society of Mechanical
        Engineers (Taiwan)</strong>, the
        <strong>International Conference on Flow Dynamics (ICFD)</strong>
        hosted by the Institute of Fluid Science, Tohoku University in Sendai,
        and to compete in domestic and international academic
        <strong>competitions</strong>.
      </p>
      <p class="mt-3">
        We welcome motivated students to work toward producing a strong
        undergraduate-research outcome — building substantive academic
        experience for graduate school, industry, or
        <strong>applications to study abroad</strong>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
